  "transliteration": "śhrī-bhagavān uvācha\nabhayaṁ sattva-saṁśhuddhir jñāna-yoga-vyavasthitiḥ\ndānaṁ damaśh cha yajñaśh cha svādhyāyas tapa ārjavam",
  "translation": "The Supreme Lord said: Fearlessness, purity of mind, steadfastness in knowledge and yoga, charity, control of the senses, sacrifice, study of sacred texts, austerity, and straightforwardness—these are the divine qualities.",
